The Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP) is not wasting any time -- it's already gearing up for the 2021 Local Government elections. UMZUMBE - The Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP) is not wasting any time -- it's already gearing up for the 2021 Local Government elections. IFP deputy president Inkosi Mzamo Buthelezi visited communities in Umzumbe, South of KwaZulu-Natal as part of a mass mobilisation campaign. READ:Â Hlabisa named new IFP leader 'We are on a mass mobilisation as the IFP where we meet people and find out about their plight so that we can take them up with the relevant departments," said Buthelezi. "We are going to take these issues up with the department nationally."
The IFP says it will be taking its mass mobilisation campaign to other parts of the country.